  [Text] Brazilian Foreign Minister <PERSON>Celso Amorim</PERSON> and 
Portuguese Foreign Minister <PERSON>Jose Durao Barroso</PERSON> have signed a 
memorandum of understanding whose main point involves the 
recognition of professions in the two countries. 
  The recognition of diplomas will be studied by the 
professional associations of the two countries. If no agreement 
is reached, the governments intend to draft specific legislation 
that will ensure the validity of registries. 
  Minister <PERSON>Celso Amorim</PERSON> noted that it will now be up to the 
Portuguese institutions to discuss the situation of these 
professionals. He noted that the agreement applies to 
professions such as attorneys-at-law, doctors, and architects. 
  The two ministers also signed an agreement that guarantees 
the promotion and protection of investments between the 
governments of <LOCATION>Brazil</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Portugal</LOCATION>. 
  Foreign Minister <PERSON>Durao Barroso</PERSON> believes that this also 
represents a great opening for <LOCATION>Brazil</LOCATION> to negotiate with other 
European nations. 

