<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> Minister <PERSON>Zenildo Zoroastro</PERSON> has ruled out any 
possibility of a coup in <LOCATION>Brazil</LOCATION>. There is no risk of 
Fujimorization in <LOCATION>Brazil</LOCATION>, the minister said, noting that 
President <PERSON>Itamar Franco</PERSON> has already said everything that had to 
be said on the subject. 
  The military ministers had thought about releasing a note 
denying the statements by Justice Minister <PERSON>Mauricio Correa</PERSON>. The 
ministers, however, preferred not to promote greater controversy 
on the subject. 

</TEXT>

